trend_summary: Built-up footprints expand steadily along the north-south highway and side roads, with new cul-de-sac subdivisions radiating into former woodland and cropland. Agricultural parcels persist but shrink, while forest edges are gradually cleared. Overall fabric shifts from scattered hamlets to a more continuous suburban corridor without reaching metropolitan compactness.
notable_changes: New housing tracts appear north and south of the central highway, increasing roof density.
Cul-de-sac road networks grow northeast, replacing patches of forest.
Several small farm fields in the eastern sector convert to residential lots.
Commercial/industrial pads emerge near the highway crossroads in the center.
Vegetation loss is visible around new ponds and drainage basins in the southwest.
